<%-layout("layouts/boilerplate.ejs")%>
    <div class="container py-4">
    <header class="mb-4">
        <h1 class="h3 mb-1">Privacy Notice</h1>
        <div class="small-muted">for <strong>Airbnb</strong></div>
        <div class="small-muted">Effective date: <strong><%=(new Date()).toISOString().slice(0,10)%></strong></div>
        <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3" role="alert">
            <strong>Friendly note:</strong> This template is for guidance only and is <em>not</em> legal advice. Please have a lawyer review it for your use case and location.
        </div>
    </header>

    <section id="intro" class="section">
        <p>
            This Privacy Notice explains how <strong>Our Company </strong>
            ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, shares, and protects your personal information when you use
            <span class="fw-semibold"> our services </span>, including our website, mobile app, and related
            services (together, the "Service"). It is written to be simple and clear.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section id="what-we-collect" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">1. Information we collect</h2>
        <h6 class="mt-3">A. Information you give us</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>Account data (name, email, password).</li>
            <li>Profile & listing data (photos, description, title, Preview, address fields) for hosts.</li>
            <li>Support requests and feedback.</li>
        </ul>
        <h6 class="mt-3">B. Information we collect automatically</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>Log data (IP address, device info, browser, pages viewed, timestamps).</li>
            <li>Usage data (clicks, searches, listings viewed, preferences).</li>
            <li>Cookies and similar technologies (see Cookies section).</li>
        </ul>
        <h6 class="mt-3">C. Information from others</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>Payment and fraud signals from payment processors.</li>
            <li>Identity verification providers (where enabled).</li>
            <li>Third‑party login providers (if you sign in with Google, Apple, etc.).</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="how-we-use" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">2. How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>To run, maintain, and improve the Service.</li>
            <li>To create and manage accounts, bookings, listings, and payments.</li>
            <li>To enable messaging between guests and hosts and to send service emails/notifications.</li>
            <li>To personalize content, show relevant listings, and remember your settings.</li>
            <li>To prevent fraud, secure the Service, and enforce our Terms.</li>
            <li>To comply with laws and respond to lawful requests.</li>
            <li>With your consent, to send marketing communications (you can opt out anytime).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="small-muted">Legal bases (for users in the EEA/UK): contract necessity, legitimate interests, consent, and legal obligation.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="sharing" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">3. Sharing & disclosure</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="fw-semibold">Between users:</span> we share necessary booking info between guests and hosts.</li>
            <li><span class="fw-semibold">Service providers:</span> we work with trusted vendors who help us operate the Service.</li>
            <li><span class="fw-semibold">Compliance & safety:</span> we may share information to meet legal requests or protect rights and safety.</li>
            <li><span class="fw-semibold">Business transfers:</span> if we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="cookies" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">4. Cookies & similar technologies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies, pixels, and local storage to keep you signed in, remember preferences, and understand how people use the Service.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Essential cookies (required for core features).</li>
            <li>Analytics cookies (help us improve).</li>
            <li>Advertising cookies (only if we run ads or remarketing — optional).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can manage cookies in your browser settings. Some features may not work without essential cookies.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="retention" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">5. Data retention</h2>
        <p>We keep your information only as long as needed for the purposes in this notice, then delete or anonymize it unless we need to keep it longer (for tax, accounting, or legal reasons).</p>
    </section>

    <section id="international" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">6. International transfers</h2>
        <p>Your information may be processed in countries other than where you live. Where required, we use appropriate safeguards (e.g., standard contractual clauses) to protect your data.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="your-rights" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">7. Your rights</h2>
        <p>You may have rights over your personal information, such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access, correction, deletion.</li>
            <li>Portability (get a copy in a usable format).</li>
            <li>Object to or restrict certain processing.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent where we rely on consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us using the details below. We may need to verify your identity.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="children" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">8. Children</h2>
        <p>Our Service is not directed to children under 18. If you believe a child provided personal information, please contact us and we will act promptly.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="security" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">9. Security</h2>
        <p>We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information. However, no online service is 100% secure.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="third-party-links" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">10. Third‑party links</h2>
        <p>Our Service may contain links to third‑party websites or services that we do not control. This notice does not cover their practices.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="changes" class="section">
        <h2 class="h5">11. Changes to this notice</h2>
        <p>We may update this Notice from time to time. We will post the new version with a new <em>Effective date</em> at the top, and, where appropriate, notify you by email or in‑app.</p>
    </section>
    <hr class="my-4" />

    <footer class="mt-4 small-muted">
        © <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Company. All rights reserved.
    </footer>
    </div>
